1
00:00:27,069 --> 00:00:30,989
片名：《桃色公寓》（又译作：公寓春光）

2
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:40,475
1959年11月1日，纽约市的人口达到了8,042,783.
On November 1, 1959, the population of New York City was 8,042,783.

3
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:45,731
如果把所有的人头尾相连按照每个人5英尺6英寸的话
If you laid them all end to end, figuring an average height of 5 feet 6 1/2 inches...

4
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:49,901
这个长度可以从时代广场一直连到巴基斯坦的卡拉奇的郊外
...they would reach from Times Square to the outskirts of Karachi, Pakistan.

5
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:54,448
我之所以很清楚这些事情，是因为我在一家名为联合生活的保险公司工作
I know facts like this because I work for an insurance company, Consolidated Life.

6
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:57,117
一家美国前五名的大公司之一
We're one of the top five companies in the country.

7
00:01:57,284 --> 00:02:01,038
我们总部有31,259名员工
Our home office has 31,259 employees...

8
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:05,500
呃，大概比密西西比河岸的那其兹的总人数还要多
...which is more than the entire population of, uh... Natchez, Mississippi.

9
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:08,629
我在19楼工作，普通保单处理部
I work on the 19th floor. Ordinary Policy Department...

10
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:12,966
保费清算分部w分区，桌号为861
...Premium Accounting Division, Section W, desk number 861.

11
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:18,055
我全名为CC·巴克斯特：C是卡尔文，C是克利夫德，但是人们一般都叫我巴德
My name is C.C. Baxter: C for Calvin, C for Clifford. But most people call me Bud.

12
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:23,435
我在这里工作了三年零十个月，我扣税后的实得工资是每周94.7美元
I've worked here three years, ten months, and my take-home pay is $94.70 a week.

13
00:02:33,612 --> 00:02:36,782
我们部门的上班时间是从8:50到17:20.
The hours in our department are 8.50 to 5.20.

14
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:46,708
16部电梯来回在每层楼忙碌，这样才能运送31,259名员工
They're staggered by floor so 16 elevators can handle the 31,259 employees...

15
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,294
而不至于交通堵塞
...without a serious traffic jam.

16
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:54,591
对于我个人而言，我一般经常待在办公室里，有时候还会加班一两个小时
As for myself, I very often stay on at the office and work for an extra hour or two...

17
00:02:54,758 --> 00:02:56,802
特别是天气很差的时候
...especially when the weather is bad.

18
00:02:56,968 --> 00:03:00,514
这不是因为我特别有野心，只是一种消磨时间的办法
It's not that I'm overly ambitious. It's just a way of killing time...

19
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,350
直到我回家时间的到来
...until it's all right for me to go home.

20
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:07,020
你看，我的公寓有一点小问题
You see, I have this little problem with my apartment.

21
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:11,775
我住在西街60号，离中心公园只有半街之隔
I live in the West 60s, just half a block from Central Park.

22
00:03:11,942 --> 00:03:15,070
我的房租是每月85美元，去年七月份还是80美元
My rent is $85 a month. It used to be $80 until last July...

23
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:19,116
直到房东太太—利伯曼夫人安装了一个二手空调后
...when Mrs. Lieberman, the landlady, put in a second-hand air conditioner.

24
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:24,913
这确实是一间好公寓，朴实无华但还是很舒适，特别适合单身汉
It's a real nice apartment. Nothing fancy, but kind of cozy. Just right for a bachelor.

25
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:28,500
唯一的问题是我不能随心所欲地随时进去
The only problem is I can't always get in when I want to.

26
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:45,600
快停下来，塞尔维亚，我们要马上出去
Cut it out, Sylvia. We've gotta get out of here.

27
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:48,770
干什么这么慌张呢？我还想喝一杯马提尼
What's the panic? I'm gonna have another martini.

28
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:51,064
求你了，塞尔维亚，现在九点过一刻了
Please, Sylvia. It's a quarter of nine.

29
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:54,526
开始你让我在这里等，然后就一直匆匆忙忙
First you can't wait to get me here and then it's rush, rush, rush.

30
00:03:54,693 --> 00:03:57,863
- 让我觉得自己是廉价的妓女　- 甜心，不是那样的
- Makes a person feel cheap. - Sweetie, it's not that.

31
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:00,782
但我答应那家伙8点整就出去的
But I promised the guy I'd be outta here by eight.

32
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:06,621
- 谁？这间公寓是谁的？　- 公司的某个傻鸟
- What guy? Whose apartment is this? - Some schnook that works in the office.

33
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:22,429
- 晚上好，巴克斯特先生　- 利伯曼夫人，你好
- Good evening, Mr. Baxter. - Mrs. Lieberman.

34
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:27,601
这糟糕的鬼天气一定是从好望角那里传过来
Some weather we're having. Must be from all that meshugaas at Cape Canaveral.

35
00:04:28,894 --> 00:04:33,648
- 你被锁在门外了吗？　- 没有，没有，只是在等一个朋友
- You're locked out of your apartment? - No, no. Just waiting for a friend.

36
00:04:34,149 --> 00:04:37,569
- 晚安，利伯曼夫人　- 晚安，巴克斯特先生
- Good night, Mrs. Lieberman. - Good night, Mr. Baxter.

37
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:58,131
- 你住在哪里？　- 我告诉过你了，和我母亲
- Where do you live? - I told you. With my mother.

38
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:01,426
- 她住在哪里？　- 布朗克斯，179街
- Where does she live? - 179th Street, in the Bronx.

39
00:05:01,593 --> 00:05:06,556
- 好的，我送你到地铁站　- 去死吧，你应该让我打的回家
- All right. I'll take you to the subway. - Like hell you will! You'll buy me a cab.

40
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:10,602
- 为什么你们这些小姐们都住在布鲁克斯呢？　- 你还带过其他的女孩到这里？
- Why do all you dames live in the Bronx? - You bring other girls up here?

41
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:13,688
当然没有，我是一个快乐的已婚男人
Certainly not. I'm a happily married man.

42
00:05:52,978 --> 00:05:56,064
你好，爵弗斯太太有什么问题吗？
- Hello there, Mrs. Dreyfuss. - Something's the matter?

43
00:05:56,231 --> 00:06:00,277
哦，我好像把钥匙放在…哈，在这里
Uh, no. I... seem to have dropped my key. Ah, here it is.

44
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:02,904
我好像听到你的房间很吵啊
Such a racket I heard in your place.

45
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:05,156
你房间是不是有小偷光顾？
Maybe you had burglars?

46
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:09,828
不要担心这个，我的房间没什么好偷的，晚安
Don't worry about that. There's nothing in here anybody'd wanna steal. Good night.

47
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:53,288
很抱歉打扰你，巴德小伙，但是开始那位小姐忘了她的手套
Sorry to bother you, Buddy-boy, but the little lady forgot her galoshes.

48
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:56,916
科克比先生，你应该八点就离开的
Mr. Kirkeby, you were supposed to be outta here by eight.

49
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:01,671
我知道，任何事情都不可能像公共汽车那么准时的
I know, but those things don't always run on schedule like a Greyhound bus.

50
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:04,424
夏天还无所谓，但是在这样的一个雨天
I don't mind in the summer, but on a rainy night...

51
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:07,218
我还没有吃晚饭呢，知道知道
- I haven't had any dinner yet. - Sure, sure.

52
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,471
哦
Oh!

53
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:12,932
我告诉你一个从人事部舍尔爵克先生那里传来的好消息
I put in a good word for you with Sheldrake in Personnel.

54
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:14,643
舍尔爵克先生对
- Mr. Sheldrake? - That's right.

55
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:18,730
我们讨论了认识调动方面的问题，我告诉他你是非常合适的人选
We discussed manpower promotionwise. I told him you're a bright boy.

56
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:22,984
他们总是在寻找合适的年轻的经理，你马上就可以被提升上去了
They're always on the lookout for young executives. You're on your way up.

57
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:26,988
而且你的酒已经被喝光了，抵押和借贷部的爱其尔伯格先生
- And you're also out of liquor. - Mr. Eichelberger, Mortgage and Loans...

58
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:31,576
昨天晚上举行了一个万圣节晚会，给我留了一些伏特加和苦艾酒
...last night he had a Halloween party. - Lay in some vodka and vermouth for me.

59
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:35,997
- 你还欠我两瓶酒呢　- 我星期五付钱给你
- You still owe me for the last two bottles. - I'll pay you on Friday.

60
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:41,461
对了，你曾经用过的那个奶酪搅拌器怎么了
Oh, and whatever happened to those little cheese crackers you used to have?

61
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,715
奶酪各搅拌器？
Cheese crackers?

62
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:26,131
干杯
Cheers.

63
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:45,900
- 晚安，巴克斯特先生　- 嗨，医生，看病这么晚回来？
- Good evening, Baxter. - Hi, Doc. Had a late call?

64
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:50,739
是的，一些小丑在斯科夫特吃三明治，总会把牙签也吃了进去
Yeah. Some clown at Schrafft's ate a club sandwich... including the toothpick.

65
00:08:52,741 --> 00:08:55,368
- 哦，晚安，医生　- 回头见，巴克斯特
- Well, good night, Doc. - Say, Baxter.

66
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:59,372
像你这样天天折腾法，估计你有一个铁打的肾
The way you're beltin' that stuff, you must have cast-iron kidneys.

67
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:03,668
那不是我，只是有时候一些朋友在我这里喝酒
That's not me. Just once in a while I have a few people in for a drink.

68
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:06,880
事实上，你也确实很厉害，铁人一个
As a matter of fact, you must be an iron man all around.

69
00:09:07,047 --> 00:09:10,258
每天从墙那边都传来那种声音，看来你好像每天都在做爱
From what I hear through the walls, you're at it every night.

70
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:14,971
不好意思吵这你们了，只是有时候我看连续两场的棒球赛
- I'm sorry if it gets noisy. - And sometimes there's a double-header.

71
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:19,059
像你一样平凡好了，回头见，医生
- A nebbish like you. - Yeah. Well, I'll see you, Doc.

72
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:22,937
对了，你知道我在哥伦比亚医学中心做研究
You know, I'm doing some research at the Columbia Medical Center.

73
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,356
- 你能帮我一个忙吗？　- 我？
- Could you do us a favor? - Me?

74
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:29,277
当你确立你的遗嘱的时候在你上天国以后，你…
When you make out your will... and the way you're going, you should...

75
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:33,531
你介意把你的遗体捐赠给大学做研究吗？
...would you mind leaving your body to the university?

76
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:38,036
我的身体？我恐怕你们要失望了。晚安，医生
My body? I'm afraid you guys'd be disappointed. Good night, Doc.

77
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:41,456
慢走，孩子
Slow down, kid.

78
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:21,996
哦，在去天堂的路上…
Oh, for heaven...

79
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:34,008
来自世界最经典电影的收藏。我们荣誉推介…
From the world's greatest library of film classics, we proudly present...

80
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,594
…由格雷塔·卡泼，约翰·白瑞莫…
...Greta Garbo, John Barrymore...

81
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:40,849
…琼·克若佛德，华莱士·比尔瑞和里昂内尔·白瑞莫…
...Joan Crawford, Wallace Beery and Lionel Barrymore...

82
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:43,810
主演的"大旅馆"。
...in "Grand Hotel".

83
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:47,021
但是首先，请我们的赞助商致辞
But first, a word from our sponsor.

84
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:51,568
如果你是时尚抽烟一族，不要被那些假冒的过滤嘴广告所欺骗
If you smoke the modern way, don't be fooled by phoney filter claims.

85
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:25,476
现在开始播放"大旅馆"，
And now, "Grand Hotel"...

86
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:28,396
由由格雷塔·卡泼，约翰·白瑞莫…
...starring Greta Garbo, John Barrymore...

87
00:11:28,563 --> 00:11:32,108
…琼·克若佛德，华菜士·比尔瑞和里昂内尔·白瑞莫主演
...Joan Crawford, Wallace Beery and Lionel Barrymore.

88
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:36,571
但是首先，请我们的第二赞助商致辞
But first, a word from our alternate sponsor.

89
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:40,408
朋友们，你有摇动的假牙吗？
Friends, do you have wobbly dentures?

90
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,227
喂，你好，巴德小伙
- Hello. - Hiya, Buddy-boy.

91
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:12,190
我现在在61街的酒吧，于是我想给你挂个电话
I'm in this bar on 61 st Street and I figured I'd give you a little buzz.

92
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:14,901
非常感谢，但是请问您是哪位？
That's very nice of you but... who is this?

93
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:17,445
多比奇.行政部的乔·多比奇
Dobisch. Joe Dobisch, in Administration.

94
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:21,407
- 哦，我听不出你的声音　- 没有问题，巴德
- Oh, yeah. I didn't recognize your voice. - That's OK, Buddy-boy.

95
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:26,120
- 我开始说过，我在61街口　- 我想我很幸运
Like I was saying, I'm in this joint on 61 st and I think I got lucky.

96
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:31,292
很抱歉，多比奇先生，我也很想帮你，可是现在太晚了
I'm sorry, Mr. Dobisch. I like to help you fellas out, but it's sort of late.

97
00:12:31,501 --> 00:12:35,755
- 我们改天再说好吗？　- 听着，小伙子，我这次控制不住
- Why don't we make it some other time? - Listen, kid. I can't pass this up.

98
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:38,633
她长得很像玛丽莲·梦露
She looks like Marilyn Monroe.

99
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:43,054
- 我已经上床睡觉了，还吃了安眠药　- 我想给你的答案是不行
I'm already in bed. And I took a sleeping pill. So I'm afraid the answer is no.

100
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:47,642
我们正在做月度绩效评估，我把你放在前十位
We're doing the monthly efficiency rating. I'm putting you in the top ten.

101
00:12:47,809 --> 00:12:49,978
你不想浪费这一机会吧，不是吗？
You don't wanna louse yourself up, do you?

102
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:54,941
不想，但是如果我晚上睡不够的话，白天怎么能高效呢
No. But how can I be efficient in the office if I don't get enough sleep at night?

103
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:59,237
现在才11点，我只借用你的地方45分钟
It's only eleven, and I just want the place for 45 minutes.

104
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:04,325
我好寂寞。你到底在和谁打电话？
I'm getting lonely. Who are you talking to, anyway?

105
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:08,496
- 我母亲　- 哦，真是甜蜜，太幸福了
- My mother. - Oh, that's sweet. That's real sweet.

106
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:10,790
嗯！
Ooh!

107
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:15,003
就是30分钟，你说怎么样，巴德？
Make it 30 minutes. What do you say, Bud, huh?

108
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:18,840
我酒喝完了，而且还没有干净的杯子
I'm all out of liquor, there's no clean glasses...

109
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:22,635
- 没有奶酪搅拌器，什么都没有　- 让我来考虑这些事情吧！
- There's no cheese crackers. No nothin'. - Let me worry about that.

110
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:25,596
你只要把钥匙放在毯子下面，然后出去就行了
Just leave the key under the mat and clear out.

111
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,849
好吧，多比奇先生
Yes, Mr. Dobisch.

112
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,436
你说什么都行，多比奇先生
Anything you say, Mr. Dobisch!

113
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:36,024
一点都不麻烦，多比奇先生，别客气
No trouble at all, Mr. Dobisch! Be my guest!

114
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:39,861
巴德小伙子从来都不会让我们失望的
We never close at Buddy-boy's.

115
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:45,658
“长的像玛丽莲·梦露”！
"Looks like Marilyn Monroe"!

116
00:14:29,077 --> 00:14:31,913
就是这个地方吗？是的
- This the place? - Yeah.

117
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,040
- 多少钱？　- 70美分
- How much? - 70 cents.

118
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:36,250
帮我拿钱，好吗？
Get the money, will you?

119
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:40,046
小心一点！
Watch those stingers!

120
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:43,424
- 给他一美元　- 谢谢，小姐
- Give him a buck. - Thanks, lady.

121
00:14:45,343 --> 00:14:47,428
帮我再放回去，宝贝！
Put it back, honey!

122
00:14:49,347 --> 00:14:51,265
太棒了
Attagirl.

123
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:54,560
- 你认为这是一个好主意？　- 没有比这更好的
- Are you sure this is a good idea? - Can't think of a better one.

124
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,938
这么晚来打扰你妈妈方便吗？
Barging in on your mother so late at night.

125
00:14:57,105 --> 00:15:01,776
不要担心老太太，只要他敢发出一声抱怨，我就让她失业
Don't worry about the old lady. One squawk from her and she's out of a job.

126
00:15:17,834 --> 00:15:19,961
帮我拿钥匙，好吗？
Get the key, will you?

127
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,797
不在那里，在地毯下面
Not there! Under the mat.

128
00:15:22,964 --> 00:15:25,758
- 在地毯下面？　- 是的，快点
- Under the mat? - Yeah. Come on.

129
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,970
把门打开，我们不能待整个晚上的。
Open up. We haven't got all night.

130
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:35,893
- 这是你母亲的公寓吗？　- 是的
- This is your mother's apartment? - That's right.

131
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:52,160
米尔德尔德，他又在里面做爱了！
Mildred! He's at it again!

132
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:45,379
- 早上好，克科比先生你好吗？　- 巴克斯特先生
- Morning, Mr. Kirkeby. - How are you, Baxter?

133
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:49,425
- 这几天你是不是很忙？　- 是的，先生，确实很忙
- They keeping you busy these days? - Yes, sir. They are indeed.

134
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:53,221
早上好，克塞尔先生，罗宾森小姐，威廉姆斯先生，李文斯顿小姐
Good morning, Mr. Kessel, Miss Robinson, Mr. Williams, Miss Livingston.

135
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:56,224
早上好，麦克维尔先生，斯库布特夫人，戴维斯先生
Good morning, Mr. McKellway, Mrs Schubert, Mr. Davis.

136
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:59,018
- 早上好，克科比先生　- 早上好，巴克斯特先生
Good morning, Mr. Kirkeby. Good morning, Mr. Baxter.

137
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:01,979
- 早上好，库伯利克小姐　- 好了，准备出发
- Morning, Miss Kubelik. - That's all. Take it away.

138
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:04,649
请小心门口，马上出发
Watch the door, please. Blasting off.

139
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:11,489
- 你的头发怎么这样了？　- 让我很不舒服，所以我绞短了它
- What did you do to your hair? - It made me nervous so I chopped it off.

140
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:14,909
- 是不是觉得不太好？　- 不是，你这个发型是我喜欢的那种
- Big mistake, huh? - No. I sort of like it. [snuffles]

141
00:17:15,076 --> 00:17:17,745
- 你很优秀　- 是的，最好不要靠太近
- You got a lulu. - Yeah. Better not get too close.

142
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:19,789
- 我从来都没有感冒　- 真的吗？
- I never catch colds. - Really?

143
00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:22,750
我读过一些疾病和意外声明数据
I was reading some sickness and accident claims figures.

144
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:27,505
平均20岁到50岁的纽约人每年都会得两次半感冒
The average New Yorker aged between 20 and 50 has two and a half colds a year.

145
00:17:27,672 --> 00:17:30,091
- 这让我感觉很恐怖　- 为什么？
- That makes me feel just terrible. - Why?

146
00:17:30,258 --> 00:17:34,470
如果我一年一次感冒都没得，那一些可怜的家伙不是要得五次感冒了
If I have no colds a year, some poor slob must have five colds a year.

147
00:17:34,637 --> 00:17:38,182
- 是的，是我　- 你今天早上应该在床上休息的
- Yeah. It's me. - You shoulda stayed in bed this morning.

148
00:17:38,349 --> 00:17:40,851
本来昨天晚上是应该睡觉的
I shoulda stayed in bed last night.

149
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:43,187
19楼！
19!

150
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,109
小心你的脚
Watch your step.

151
00:17:48,276 --> 00:17:50,778
- 小心你的手，克科比先生　- 再说一遍？
- And watch your hands, Mr. Kirkeby! - Pardon?

152
00:17:50,945 --> 00:17:54,490
有一天我想用这门把你夹住
One of these days I'm gonna shut these doors on you and...

153
00:17:56,701 --> 00:17:58,494
下一站20层
20 next!

154
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:02,873
那个库伯利克小姐，小伙子，我想和她一起坐到中国的电梯
That Kubelik. Boy, would I like to get her on a slow elevator to China!

155
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:06,627
她是这栋楼最漂亮的操作员，我也很优秀
- She's the best operator in the building. - I'm pretty good myself.

156
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:09,797
但她从来都不和我约会，也许你能行
- But she won't give me a date. - Maybe it's your approach.

157
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:13,718
她周围很多人试过各种办法，结果都不行
A lot of guys around here have tried all kinds of approaches. No dice.

158
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:18,014
- 她想要证明什么？　- 她是一个很值得爱的女孩
- What's she trying to prove? - She could just be a nice respectable girl.

159
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,725
听他说过！小罗的佛特劳瑞
Listen to him! Little Lord Fauntleroy.

160
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,920
您好，多比奇先生，我是19层的巴克斯特先生
Hello. Mr. Dobisch? This is Baxter on the 19th floor.

161
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,797
哦，巴德小伙
Oh, Buddy-boy!

162
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:56,844
我正想给你打电话呢！不好意思把你的卧室墙上弄得这么脏
I was just about to call you. I'm sorry about that mess on the living room wall.

163
00:18:57,011 --> 00:19:01,182
我的朋友坚持认为毕加索是个游民，于是她开始在墙上作壁画
My friend kept insisting Picasso was a bum, so she started to do that mural.

164
00:19:01,349 --> 00:19:03,726
我不是为了毕加索
It's not Picasso I'm calling about.

165
00:19:03,893 --> 00:19:08,647
我来要我公寓的钥匙，你说好要放在地毯下面
It's the key to my apartment. You're supposed to leave it under the mat.

166
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:11,859
我放了，我清清楚楚的记得放过了
But I did. I distinctly remember putting it there.

167
00:19:12,026 --> 00:19:15,154
哦，我也找到钥匙，不过不是我的钥匙
Oh, I found the key all right. Only it's the wrong key!

168
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:21,452
是吗？怪不得我今天早上进不了经理盥洗室
It is? No wonder I couldn't get into the executive washroom this morning.

169
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:24,038
但是我却进不了我的公寓
And I couldn't get into my apartment!

170
00:19:24,205 --> 00:19:28,167
于是早上四点我叫醒房东太太，撒了很多不着边际的谎言来骗她
So at 4am I gotta wake up the landlady and give her a whole song and dance.

171
00:19:28,334 --> 00:19:31,504
不好意思我会派人送给你正确的房间钥匙
That's a shame. I'll send the key right down.

172
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:33,547
关于你的提升报告
And about your promotion.

173
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:36,884
我会把绩效评估报告送给人事部的舍尔爵克先生
I'll send that efficiency report to Mr. Sheldrake in Personnel.

174
00:19:37,051 --> 00:19:39,512
你在今天之前应该可以听到好消息
You may hear from him before the day's over.

175
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:41,722
谢谢，多比奇先生
Thank you, Mr. Dobisch.

176
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,668
多比奇先生给你的
From Mr. Dobisch.

177
00:20:10,835 --> 00:20:12,920
等一下
Wait.

178
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:25,599
给多比奇先生的
For Mr. Dobisch.

179
00:20:32,273 --> 00:20:34,400
嗯哼，嗯哼
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

180
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:50,875
万德豪夫，公共关系部
Vanderhof. Public Relations.

181
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:53,002
哦，是巴克斯特，等我一下
Oh, yes, Baxter. Just a minute.

182
00:20:53,169 --> 00:20:56,547
好的，芬奇小姐把我们说好的这些打印好
All right, Miss Finch. Type up what we got so far.

183
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:01,385
看，原来我给你安排在今天晚上的
Look, I've got you down for tonight...

184
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:04,805
但是我今天晚上要自己用公寓，所以我必须取消你预定的时间
...but I'll be using the place myself, so I'll have to cancel.

185
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:07,892
但是今天是她的生日，我已经定了蛋糕
But it's her birthday. I already ordered the cake.

186
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:13,147
但是我病了，得了重感冒还发烧，我必须要在工作后回家睡觉
But I am sick. I got a terrible cold and a fever. I got to go to bed right after work.

187
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:16,984
如果你得了感冒，你应该去泡一晚上土耳其浴，好好出出汗
If you got a cold, you go to a Turkish bath. Spend the night. Sweat it out.

188
00:21:17,151 --> 00:21:21,322
那是你为什么会得肺炎的原因。如果我得了肺炎，那我就要躺上一个月了
That's how you get pneumonia. If I got pneumonia, I'd be in bed for a month.

189
00:21:21,489 --> 00:21:25,826
好的，你说得有道理，我在下个星期三晚上可以吗？
OK. You made your point. We'll just have to do it next Wednesday night.

190
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:31,665
- 只有那天我才有空　- 星期三，星期三…星期三
- It's the only night I can get away. - Wednesday, Wednesday... Wednesday.

191
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:35,503
已经有人预订了
I got somebody penciled in.

192
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:38,589
让我来安排一下，我马上给你回复
Let me see what I can do. I'll get back to you.

193
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:53,020
- 爱奇尔伯格先生　- 哦，是巴克斯特，有什么事情？
- Mr. Eichelberger. - Oh, yes, Baxter. What's your problem?

194
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:59,944
星期三不行？天啊，这把我的日程弄得一团糟
Wednesday is out? Oh, that throws a little monkey wrench into my agenda.

195
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:03,447
星期四？不行，那一整天我都没有空
Thursday? No, I'm all tied up on Thursday.

196
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:07,993
让我来排排时间，呃，在星期五怎么样？
Let's schedule that, uh... meeting for Friday.

197
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,204
星期五
Friday.

198
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:13,874
让我来盘算一下，等一下给你回复
Let me see what I can do. I'll get back to you.

199
00:22:19,547 --> 00:22:24,385
在保险金和保单种类方面，我们比去年增长了18%
Premiumwise and billingwise, we are 18 percent ahead of last year Octoberwise.

200
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:30,224
喂？哦，巴克斯特，有什么事情？
Hello? Yeah, Baxter. What's up?

201
00:22:30,391 --> 00:22:33,561
我把你的时间从星期五调到星期四如何？
Instead of Friday, could you possibly switch to Thursday?

202
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:36,564
你帮了我一个大忙了
You'd be doing me a great favor.

203
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:39,483
然我来看看，等下回复你
Let me check. I'll get back to you.

204
00:22:41,235 --> 00:22:43,696
联合生活，我以后联系你
Consolidated Life. I'll connect you.

205
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:45,739
塞尔维亚，你的电话
Sylvia, it's for you.

206
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:47,700
喂？
Yeah?

207
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:49,493
你好
Oh, hello.

208
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:52,913
我当然自己回家了，你欠我45美分
Sure I got home all right. You owe me 45 cents.

209
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:56,876
听着，塞尔维亚，不在星期五，我们星期四晚上如何？
Look, Sylvia. Instead of Friday, could we make it Thursday night?

210
00:22:57,084 --> 00:23:02,256
星期四？！那好吧，那就取消和鲍勃·斯戴布的约会！
Thursday?! Well, that's The Untouchables with Bob Stack!

211
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:04,592
鲍勃是谁？
Bob who?

212
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:08,762
好的，那我们在公寓碰面，有什么了不起！
All right, so we'll watch it at the apartment. Big deal!

213
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:15,603
喂，巴克斯特吗？星期四可以了
Hello, Baxter? It's OK for Thursday.

214
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:18,272
谢谢，克科比先生
Thank you, Mr. Kirkeby.

215
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:30,451
爱奇尔伯格先生，星期五可以了
Mr. Eichelberger, it's OK for Friday.

216
00:23:37,917 --> 00:23:40,794
万德豪夫先生，星期三可以了
Mr. Vanderhof? OK for Wednesday.

217
00:23:51,764 --> 00:23:53,599
好的，我会告诉他的
All right. I'll tell him.

218
00:23:53,766 --> 00:23:57,561
嗨，巴克斯特，人事部舍尔爵克先生的秘书给你打了电话
Hey, Baxter, that was Personnel. Mr. Sheldrake's secretary.

219
00:23:57,728 --> 00:24:02,733
她在开始的20分钟里一直想找你，他们让你上楼
She's been trying to reach you for the last 20 minutes. They want you upstairs.

220
00:24:03,525 --> 00:24:08,405
- 你要升职，还是被炒鱿鱼？　- 那我们来小赌一把如何？
- Are you getting promoted? Or fired? - Would you care to make a small wager?

221
00:24:08,572 --> 00:24:12,701
- 我在这里待的时间是你的两倍，但是…　- 赌一美元如何？
- I've been here twice as long as you but... - Let's say a dollar?

222
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:14,495
赌就赌！
It's a bet!

223
00:24:28,509 --> 00:24:30,803
- 上去吗？　- 哦，对不起
- Going up? - Oh! Excuse me.

224
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:36,183
27楼，谢谢！小心一点，你在运送一件重要的货物，也就是指大人物
27, please. Drive carefully. You're carrying precious cargo. I mean manpowerwise.

225
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,435
27楼.
27.

226
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:42,523
看不出来吧，我是公司业绩评估的前十名…
You may not realize it, but I am in the top ten, efficiencywise...

227
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:45,442
今天我很有可能被提升
...and this may be the day promotionwise.

228
00:24:45,609 --> 00:24:48,195
你说话已经开始像克科比先生了
You're beginning to sound like Mr. Kirkeby already.

229
00:24:48,362 --> 00:24:52,366
- 为什么不呢，当他们把我送到楼上。　- 为什么这种事情不能发生在一个好人身上呢
- Why not, as they're kicking me upstairs? - Couldn't happen to a nicer guy.

230
00:24:52,533 --> 00:24:56,203
你知道，你是电梯里唯一脱帽的人
You know, you're the only one who takes his hat off in the elevator.

231
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:58,664
这是电梯里男人们的事情
Something happens to men in elevators.

232
00:24:58,831 --> 00:25:01,792
这是地位改变的缘故，血都冲到他们的头上了
It's the change of altitude. The blood rushes to their head.

233
00:25:01,959 --> 00:25:05,129
- 我可以给你讲一些故事　- 我很乐意听
- I could tell you stories... - I'd love to hear 'em.

234
00:25:05,295 --> 00:25:07,840
我们什么时候在外面吃顿饭如何
We could have lunch in the cafeteria sometime.

235
00:25:08,007 --> 00:25:09,883
或者在工作后的某个晚上
Or some evening, after work?

236
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:12,553
- 27楼到　- 哦
- 27. - Oh.

237
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,347
- 我希望你一切顺利　- 我也希望如此
- I hope everything goes all right. - I hope so.

238
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:18,225
他们今天给我打电话，我的感冒也好些了
They would call me today, what with my cold.

239
00:25:18,392 --> 00:25:20,894
- 我看起来精神吗？　- 很好，等一下
- How do I look? - Fine. Wait.

240
00:25:21,729 --> 00:25:23,230
谢谢！
Thank you.

241
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:28,235
我注意到了，当你在电梯上的时候，你总会戴一朵小花
I noticed, when you were still on the local elevator, you always wore a flower.

242
00:25:28,402 --> 00:25:30,904
祝你好运，把你的鼻子擦干净
Good luck. And wipe your nose.

243
00:25:46,587 --> 00:25:50,049
CC·巴克斯特，普通保费清算部，舍尔爵克先生叫我
C.C. Baxter, Ordinary Premium Accounting. Mr. Sheldrake called me.

244
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,926
我找你，而且我都找你20分钟了
I called you. That is, I tried to for 20 minutes.

245
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:55,220
- 不好意思　- 进去吧
- I'm sorry. - Go on in.

246
00:26:06,899 --> 00:26:08,442
- 巴克斯特？　- 是的，先生
- Baxter? - Yes, sir.

247
00:26:08,609 --> 00:26:10,694
进来，进来
Come in, come in.

248
00:26:11,612 --> 00:26:14,531
我正在想你长什么样子，巴克斯特
I was sort of wondering what you looked like, Baxter.

249
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:17,242
- 请坐　- 谢谢，舍尔爵克先生
- Sit down. - Yes, Mr. Sheldrake.

250
00:26:18,702 --> 00:26:21,413
我听说一些人都说你很优秀
Been hearing some nice things about you.

251
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:24,625
克比奇先生说你忠诚，富有合作精神，很有潜力
Mr. Dobisch says you're loyal, cooperative, resourceful.

252
00:26:24,792 --> 00:26:29,129
- 他这么说？　- 克科比先生说你经常加班
- Mr. Dobisch said that? - Mr. Kirkeby tells me you often work late...

253
00:26:29,296 --> 00:26:32,633
- 却不领加班费　- 你知道的，事情总是一大堆
...without overtime. - You know how it is. Things pile up.

254
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:36,887
公共关系部的万德豪夫先生，抵押和借贷部的爱奇尔伯格先生
Mr. Vanderhof in Public Relations and Mr. Eichelberger in Mortgage and Loans...

255
00:26:37,054 --> 00:26:39,932
都希望你能调到他们的部门
...would both like you transferred to their departments.

256
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,059
太过奖了
Very flattering.

257
00:26:43,102 --> 00:26:47,314
告诉我，巴克斯特，究竟是什么原因让你这么受人欢迎？
Tell me, Baxter. Just what is it that makes you so popular?

258
00:26:47,481 --> 00:26:50,943
- 我不知道　- 想一想
- I don't know. - Think.

259
00:26:56,156 --> 00:27:00,160
- 你能在重复一下问题吗？　- 听着，巴克斯特，我并不傻
- Would you mind repeating the question? - Look, Baxter. I'm not stupid.

260
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:04,832
我知道这栋大楼每年每天发生的事情
I know everything that goes on in this building every day of the year.

261
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,458
真的吗？
You do?

262
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:11,130
1957年我们这里有一个雇员，名叫弗劳尔，他也很受欢迎
In 1957 we had an employee here, name of Fowler. He was very popular too.

263
00:27:11,296 --> 00:27:13,966
后来才知道他在开一个赌马的投注点
It turned out he was running a bookie joint...

264
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:17,636
连上我们的接线总机，并用我们的IBM计算机来计算冷门
...tying up our switchboard, using our IBM machines to figure the odds.

265
00:27:17,803 --> 00:27:22,015
在肯塔基德比赛的前一天我告诉了刑警队，他们逮捕了他
The day before the Kentucky Derby I called in the vice squad, who raided him.

266
00:27:22,182 --> 00:27:24,184
- 刑警队？　- 是的
- The vice squad? - That's right.

267
00:27:24,351 --> 00:27:27,646
这和我有什么关系呢？我没有开任何一个赌马的投注点
What's that got to do with me? I'm not running any bookie joint.

268
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:31,275
那你开的是哪种中介站呢？先生？
- Just what kind of joint are you running? - Sir?

269
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:36,488
一个联结从克科比到万德豪夫，到艾奇尔伯格，再到多比奇的关键东西
A key is floating around from Kirkeby to Vanderhof to Eichelberger to Dobisch.

270
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,574
这个东西好像是一间公寓
It's the key to a certain apartment.

271
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:42,202
- 知道公寓是谁的吗？　- 谁？
- Know who that apartment belongs to? - Who?

272
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:45,706
忠诚的，极具潜力和合作精神的CC·巴克斯特先生
Loyal, resourceful, cooperative C.C. Baxter.

273
00:27:48,208 --> 00:27:50,711
- 哦　- 你打算否认这一切吗？
- Oh. - Are you going to deny it?

274
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:55,716
不，我不想否认这一切，如果你能给我一个解释的机会
No. I'm not going to deny it. If you'd just let me explain.

275
00:27:56,341 --> 00:27:58,135
说吧！
You'd better.

276
00:27:58,302 --> 00:28:00,387
好
Well...

277
00:28:01,013 --> 00:28:05,726
大约一年前，我正在上夜校，学习高级会计
...about a year ago, I was going to night school, studying advanced accounting.

278
00:28:05,893 --> 00:28:10,898
我们部门的一个住在泽西的家伙，要参加镇上的一个晚宴
One of the guys in our department... lives in Jersey... had to go to a banquet in town.

279
00:28:11,064 --> 00:28:15,402
他需要一个地方来换燕尾服，于是我把钥匙借给了他
He needed someplace to change into a tuxedo, so I gave him the key.

280
00:28:15,569 --> 00:28:21,533
这个消息一下全传开了，忽然间所有人都要参加晚宴
Word must've gotten out because all sorts of guys were suddenly going to banquets.

281
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:26,580
你把钥匙给了这个人，你就不能拒绝另外一个，事情终于无法控制
You give the key to one guy, you can't say no to another. It all got out of hand.

282
00:28:29,583 --> 00:28:32,920
巴克斯特，一个保险公司是建立在公众信任之上的
Baxter, an insurance company is founded on public trust.

283
00:28:33,086 --> 00:28:36,381
一个雇员的行为如果不典的话
Any employee who conducts himself in a manner unbecoming...

284
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:39,551
你们这一个小团体有几个人？
How many charter members are there in this little club?

285
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:43,430
只有四个，31,259人中的四个
Just those four. Out of a total of 31,259.

286
00:28:43,597 --> 00:28:47,684
所以我们应该为我们的员工自豪，这个比例很小
So actually we can be very proud of our personnel... percentagewise.

287
00:28:47,851 --> 00:28:52,439
但这不是重点，一个篮子中的四个烂苹果，不管这个篮子有多大…
That's not the point. Four rotten apples in a barrel, however large the barrel...

288
00:28:52,606 --> 00:28:55,776
- 你意识到这有多大的损害　- 不会的
- Do you realize if this ever leaked out... - It won't!

289
00:28:55,943 --> 00:29:00,948
相信我，再也不会了，从现在开始没有人会用我的钥匙
Believe me. Never again. Nobody is gonna use my apartment from now on.

290
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:03,742
- 你的公寓在哪里？　- 西67街
- Where is your apartment? - West 67th Street.

291
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:09,331
你不知道我是怎么和邻居和房东太太处理关于钥匙的事情
You have no idea what I go through with the neighbors, the landlady and the key.

292
00:29:09,498 --> 00:29:11,500
你是怎么把钥匙给他们的？
How do you work it with the key?

293
00:29:11,667 --> 00:29:16,546
我把钥匙在办公室的时候给他们，他们走的时候放在毯子下面，我保证再也不会了
I slip it to 'em in the office and they leave it under a mat. Never again. I promise.

294
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:24,262
- 奥尔森小姐，有什么事情？　- 舍尔爵克太太，在2线给你回电话.
- Yes, Miss Olsen? - Mrs. Sheldrake, returning your call. On 2.

295
00:29:28,725 --> 00:29:30,894
亲爱的，你在哪里呢？
Yes, dear. Where were you?

296
00:29:31,645 --> 00:29:36,400
你应该带托米看牙医的？没有虫牙？好的，等一下，亲爱的。
You had to take Tommy to the dentist? No cavities? Good. Hold it, dear.

297
00:29:36,566 --> 00:29:39,569
- 你去哪里，巴克斯特先生？　- 我不想打扰你
- Where are you going, Baxter? - I don't wanna intrude.

298
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:42,990
- 既然事情已经清楚了　- 我和你还有事情
- Since this is straightened out... - I'm not through with you yet.

299
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:45,325
我今天晚上不能回家吃晚饭了
I won't be home for dinner tonight.

300
00:29:45,492 --> 00:29:49,496
从堪萨斯来的分部经理今天在这里，我要陪他去看戏
The branch manager from Kansas City is in town. I'm taking him to the theater.

301
00:29:49,663 --> 00:29:51,456
剧名叫《音乐人》，还有什么事情吗？
Music Man. What else?

302
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:54,167
不，不要等我，亲爱的，再见
No, don't wait up for me, darling. Goodbye.

303
00:29:55,335 --> 00:29:58,755
告诉我，巴克斯特你看过《音乐人》这部戏吗？
Tell me, Baxter. Have you seen Music Man?

304
00:29:58,922 --> 00:30:01,508
还没有，不过听说很不错
Not yet. I hear it's one swell show.

305
00:30:01,675 --> 00:30:03,844
今天晚上你去怎么样？
How would you like to go tonight?

306
00:30:04,011 --> 00:30:08,307
你和我吗？我想你要陪那位从堪萨斯来的经理吧！
You and me? I thought you were taking the branch manager from Kansas City.

307
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:11,685
不，我有其他的事情，你可以把这两张票都拿去
No, I have other plans. You can have both tickets.

308
00:30:11,852 --> 00:30:13,854
哦，你太好了
Well... that's very kind of you.

309
00:30:14,021 --> 00:30:18,025
但是我今天身体不太舒服，感冒了，我只想马上回家休息
But I'm not feeling well. I've got this cold. I'm gonna go right home.

310
00:30:18,191 --> 00:30:21,862
巴克斯特，你没有弄懂我的意思，我告诉你有计划的
Baxter, you're not reading me. I told you I have plans.

311
00:30:22,195 --> 00:30:25,365
我也是，我就想吃四片阿斯匹林，然后上床睡觉
So do I. I'm gonna take four aspirins, get into bed.

312
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:27,868
那您把票给别人吧！
So give the tickets to somebody else.

313
00:30:28,201 --> 00:30:32,873
听着，巴克斯特，我不是想白给你票，我想和你交换
Look, Baxter. I'm not just giving these tickets. I wanna swap them.

314
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:35,208
交换？换什么？
Swap 'em? For what?

315
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:42,382
他们还说你头脑机敏，狡猾还非常有想象力
It also says here that you are alert, astute and quite imaginative.

316
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:45,552
哦？
Oh?

317
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:52,642
哦
Oh...

318
00:31:02,027 --> 00:31:06,073
这就对了，巴克斯特，下个月人事部会有一个调动的机会
That's good thinking, Baxter. There's gonna be a shift in personnel next month.

319
00:31:06,239 --> 00:31:10,077
据我所知你是一个当经理的好材料
And as far as I'm concerned, you are executive material.

320
00:31:10,243 --> 00:31:12,746
- 我？　- 现在你把钥匙留下
- I am? - Now put down the key.

321
00:31:15,916 --> 00:31:17,959
写好你的地址
And put down the address.

322
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:25,133
我的公寓在二楼，门上什么都没有，只写着公寓2A。
It's on the second floor. There's no name over the door. It just says apartment 2A.

323
00:31:26,009 --> 00:31:28,053
很冷吗？放松点，巴克斯特
- It's that cold. - Relax, Baxter.

324
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:30,263
好的，谢谢
Yes, thank you, sir.

325
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:35,352
你们应该注意点唱片机，小声点，否则邻居会抱怨的
You will be careful with the record player? Shh.

326
00:31:35,519 --> 00:31:37,521
对了，还有酒的问题
Oh, and about the liquor.

327
00:31:37,687 --> 00:31:42,275
我今天上午已经预订了，我不知道他们会什么时候送过来
I ordered some this morning. I don't know when they'll deliver it.

328
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:46,279
- 这是我们的小秘密　- 当然
- This is going to be our little secret. - Of course.

329
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:49,116
- 你知道人言可畏　- 不要担心
- You know how people talk. - Don't worry about that.

330
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:52,953
- 我没有什么好隐藏的　- 是，总之，这不关我的事
- Not that I have anything to hide. - No! Anyway, it's none of my business.

331
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:56,957
4个人，5个人，有什么区别呢？
Four apples, five apples. What's the difference?

332
00:31:57,124 --> 00:31:59,126
很好的比率
Percentagewise.

333
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:01,837
给你，巴克斯特先生，玩得愉快
Here you are, Baxter. Have a nice time.

334
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:04,131
你也一样，先生
You too, sir.

335
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:40,000
我认为担任像他这种职位的人，他会带我去摩洛哥，可能是21。
So I figure, a man in his position, he'll take me to El Morocco, maybe 21.

336
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:44,796
结果他却带我去什么汉堡天堂和一个傻瓜的公寓
Instead he takes me to Hamburger Heaven and some schnook's apartment.

337
00:32:49,676 --> 00:32:51,803
- 晚安　- 晚安
- Good night. - Good night.

338
00:32:53,763 --> 00:32:56,057
嘿，库伯利克小姐
Oh! Miss Kubelik?

339
00:32:56,224 --> 00:32:59,352
我一直在等你，都差一点认不出你了
I've been waiting for you. I almost didn't recognize you.

340
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:02,689
这是第一次我看你穿便装
This is the first time I've seen you in civilian clothes.

341
00:33:02,856 --> 00:33:05,066
- 到27楼结果如何？　- 非常好
- How'd it go on the 27th floor? - Great.

342
00:33:05,233 --> 00:33:07,652
- 你看过《音乐人》吗？　- 没有
- Look, have you seen The Music Man? - No.

343
00:33:07,819 --> 00:33:09,362
- 那你想不想去看呢？　- 当然
- Would you like to? - Sure.

344
00:33:09,529 --> 00:33:11,865
我们可以先去吃点什么然后再去看戏
We could get a bite to eat first, and then go.

345
00:33:12,032 --> 00:33:13,533
- 哦，你是说今晚吗？　- 对啊！
- Oh, you mean tonight? - Yeah.

346
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:16,786
- 不好意思，恐怕不行，我已经约了别人　- 太糟糕了
- I'm sorry, I can't. I'm meeting somebody. - Oh.

347
00:33:16,953 --> 00:33:20,498
- 你是指，和你的…你的女性朋友约会？　- 不，一个男的
- You mean... like a girlfriend? - No. Like a man.

348
00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:25,212
我想这不是我个人的意见，公司的同事都在想你是否已经…
I wasn't trying to be personal. The fellas in the office were wondering if you ever...

349
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:27,297
你随便什么时候告诉他们
You tell 'em now and then.

350
00:33:27,464 --> 00:33:31,718
这个约会…就是一个约会？有什么很严重的问题吗？
This date, is it... just a date? Or is it something serious?

351
00:33:31,885 --> 00:33:35,347
哦，曾经是一个很严重的问题，至少对我是的，但对他就不是
Well, it used to be serious. At least, I was. But he wasn't.

352
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:37,849
所以现在整件事情多多少少，意义都不大了
So now the whole thing's more or less kaput.

353
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:40,560
- 如果那样的话，你能不能…　- 恐怕不行
- In that case, couldn't you... - I'm afraid not.

354
00:33:40,727 --> 00:33:44,898
我答应他和他喝酒的，他已经约我一个星期了
I promised I'd have a drink with him. He's been calling me all week.

355
00:33:45,565 --> 00:33:47,734
我明白
I understand.

356
00:33:47,901 --> 00:33:52,405
哦，这只是我的建议，我不想看到这两张戏票浪费
Well, it was just an idea. I hate to see a theater ticket go to waste.

357
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:55,659
- 这场戏什么时候开始？　- 20:30
- What time does the show go on? - 8:30.

358
00:33:55,825 --> 00:33:58,161
好吧，我尽可能到戏院找你
Well, I could meet you at the theatre.

359
00:33:58,328 --> 00:34:02,374
太好了，就在44街
That's wonderful! It's the Majestic on 44th Street.

360
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,376
我在大堂等你
I'll meet you in the lobby.

361
00:34:04,543 --> 00:34:08,004
你知道的，早上我的精神很差，好像得了101感冒
You know, I felt so lousy this morning. Had 101 fever.

362
00:34:08,171 --> 00:34:11,591
现在我得到了升迁，并且还有11排中间的座位
Now along comes my promotion and us... 11 th row centre.

363
00:34:11,758 --> 00:34:13,718
你还说我要躺在床上休息
And you said I should've stayed in bed.

364
00:34:13,885 --> 00:34:16,012
- 你感冒怎样了？　- 什么感冒
- How is your cold? - What cold?

365
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:20,183
看完戏我还能在镇上到处逛逛
After the show we could go out on the town. [hums dance tune]

366
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:23,103
- 我从亚瑟莫里那里得到了力量　- 我明白
- I've been taking from Arthur Murray. - So I see.

367
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:26,231
在村上的EI奇科有一支很好的乐队
There's a great band at El Chico, in the Village.

368
00:34:26,398 --> 00:34:29,901
- 就在你家附近的拐口处　- 听起来很不错
- Around the corner from where you live. - Sounds good.

369
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:34,614
- 你怎么知道我住在哪里？　- 哦，…我甚至知道你和谁一起住
- How do you know where I live? - Oh, I... even know who you live with.

370
00:34:34,781 --> 00:34:36,783
你姐姐和姐夫
Your sister and brother-in-law.

371
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:40,912
我知道你什么时候在哪里生的，我知道所有关于你的事情
I know when you were born and where. I know all sorts of things about you.

372
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:42,455
你怎么知道这些的？
How come?

373
00:34:42,622 --> 00:34:47,294
几个月前在集团的人身保险里，我看到了你的资料卡片
A couple of months ago I looked up your card in the group insurance file.

374
00:34:47,460 --> 00:34:51,298
我知道你的身高体重，你的社保号码
I know your height and your weight and your social security number.

375
00:34:51,464 --> 00:34:55,468
你得过腮腺炎和麻疹，你的阑尾已经被割掉了
You had mumps and measles and you had your appendix out.

376
00:34:56,386 --> 00:34:59,472
不要给公司的那帮家伙说我割了阑尾
Don't mention the appendix to the fellas in the office.

377
00:34:59,639 --> 00:35:04,477
我不想让人家在那里乱猜：你是怎么知道我割了阑尾？再见！
I wouldn't want 'em to get the wrong idea about how you found out. Bye.

378
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:09,816
20:30！
8:30!

379
00:35:58,698 --> 00:36:02,786
- 晚上好，舍尔爵克先生　- 弗兰，请不要这么大声
- Good evening, Mr. Sheldrake. - Please, Fran. Not so loud.

380
00:36:02,952 --> 00:36:05,372
你还害怕有人看到我们在一起？
Still afraid someone might see us together?

381
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:09,209
- 我来帮你放大衣　- 不，杰夫，我不能待太久
- Let me take your coat. - No, Jeff. I can't stay very long.

382
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:13,713
- 我能喝一杯冰冻的待克瑞鸡尾酒吗？　- 马上就到
- Can I have a frozen daiquiri? - It's on the way.

383
00:36:14,798 --> 00:36:18,218
- 我看到你走过来，而且头发已经剪短了　- 没错
- I see you went ahead and cut your hair. - That's right.

384
00:36:18,385 --> 00:36:21,680
- 你知道我更喜欢你留长头发的　- 我知道
- You know I liked it better long. - I know.

385
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:24,724
你还想你的钱包有一个锁呢！
You want a lock to carry in your wallet?

386
00:36:25,475 --> 00:36:29,062
- 晚上好，女士，很高兴再次看到你　- 谢谢
- Evening, lady. Nice to see you again. - Thank you.

387
00:36:30,146 --> 00:36:32,399
已经有多久了，弗兰？一个月吗？
How long has it been, Fran? A month?

388
00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:35,235
6个星期，那有什么意义呢
Six weeks. But who's counting?

389
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:38,405
我想你
I missed you.

390
00:36:40,907 --> 00:36:42,909
老土
Like old times.

391
00:36:43,076 --> 00:36:45,829
同样的座位，同样的音乐
Same booth. Same song.

392
00:36:46,663 --> 00:36:50,834
- 糟糕透了　- 同样酸甜的沙司
- It's been hell. - Same sauce. Sweet-and-sour.

393
00:36:53,336 --> 00:36:56,464
你不知道那是什么感觉，在电梯里与你隔肩而立
You don't know what it's like, next to you in that elevator.

394
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:59,843
“早上好，库伯利克小姐。”“晚上好，舍尔爵克先生。”
"Good morning, Miss Kubelik." "Good night, Mr. Sheldrake."

395
00:37:00,009 --> 00:37:02,512
弗兰，我对你仍是一往情深
I'm still crazy about you, Fran.

396
00:37:02,679 --> 00:37:08,226
- 杰夫，请不要开始就这样说，好吗？　- 我只是开始讲述我对你的真情
Let's not start on that again, Jeff. Please? I'm just beginning to get over it.

397
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:12,021
鬼才信你
I don't believe you.

398
00:37:13,189 --> 00:37:16,109
听者，杰夫，这个夏天的两个月，我们过得很开心
Look, Jeff. We had two wonderful months this summer.

399
00:37:16,276 --> 00:37:19,112
但是那都已经过去了
But that was it. Happens all the time.

400
00:37:19,279 --> 00:37:23,408
妻子和孩子一出国旅游，老板就可以和他的秘书…
Wife and kids go away to the country and the boss has a fling with his secretary...

401
00:37:23,575 --> 00:37:26,286
…或者发廊妹，或者电梯小姐偷欢.
...or the manicurist, or the elevator girl.

402
00:37:26,453 --> 00:37:29,789
九月份来到的时候，野餐结束了，也是说再见的时候了
Come September, the picnic's over. Goodbye.

403
00:37:29,956 --> 00:37:33,960
子女们要重新回到学校，老板也要回到他夫人的身边…
The kids go back to school, the boss goes back to the wife...

404
00:37:34,127 --> 00:37:36,254
…至于那可怜的女孩
...and the girl...

405
00:37:37,547 --> 00:37:40,592
他们再也不会像以往一样，做她爱吃的龙虾
They don't make these shrimp like they used to.

406
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:46,431
弗兰，我从来都没有说分手
I never said goodbye, Fran.

407
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:53,271
有那么一段时间，你开玩笑说，说你快乐得像一个单身汉
For a while there, you try kidding yourself that you're going with an unmarried man.

408
00:37:53,438 --> 00:37:56,149
然后，有一天他就开始不停地看表
Then one day he keeps looking at his watch...

409
00:37:56,316 --> 00:37:58,943
…并问我你身上是不是还有口红的痕迹。
...and asks you if any lipstick's showing...

410
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:02,655
…然后就冲出去，去赶开往白色平原的火车
...then rushes out to catch the 7:14 to White Plains.

411
00:38:03,823 --> 00:38:07,327
就像喝一杯速溶咖啡一样潇洒…
So you fix yourself a cup of instant coffee...

412
00:38:07,494 --> 00:38:11,331
…你坐在那里，然后在想…
...and you sit there by yourself and you think...

413
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:15,627
…一切看起来都是那么的无聊.
...and it all begins to look so... ugly.

414
00:38:19,088 --> 00:38:22,842
你知道我赶19:14回家的火车是什么感受吗？
How do you think I felt riding home on that 7:14 train?

415
00:38:23,009 --> 00:38:27,180
杰夫，你为什么还要给我打电话？你还要我怎么样？
Why do you keep calling me, Jeff? What do you want from me?

416
00:38:27,347 --> 00:38:29,349
弗兰，我想你回到我身边
I want you back, Fran.

417
00:38:29,516 --> 00:38:33,436
不好意思，舍尔爵克先生，我现在很忙，你应该去找另外一个人去了
Sorry, Mr. Sheldrake. I'm full up. You'll have to take the next elevator.

418
00:38:33,603 --> 00:38:37,482
弗兰，你都不给我一个机会，我有一些事情要告诉你
You're not giving me a chance, Fran. I have something to tell you.

419
00:38:37,649 --> 00:38:41,486
- 快说啊，什么事情　- 不在这里，我们能换一个地方吗？
- Go ahead. Tell me. - Not here. Can't we go someplace else?

420
00:38:41,653 --> 00:38:44,531
- 不行，我在8:30还有一个约会　- 什么？
- No. I have a date at 8:30. - Oh?

421
00:38:44,864 --> 00:38:48,660
- 很重要吗？　- 不是，但是我不能爽约.
- Important? - Not very, but I'm gonna be there anyway.

422
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:51,454
- 你想现在吃东西吗？　- 不，我不想吃
- You ready order dinner now? - No. No dinner.

423
00:38:51,621 --> 00:38:54,165
再来两杯，好吗？
Just bring us two more drinks, will you?

424
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:16,896
弗兰，你还记得我们在一起的那个周末吗？
Fran, do you remember that last weekend we had?

425
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:21,901
我记得！你租的那条破船，让我穿着黑色的睡衣，还戴着救生圈
Do I! That leaky boat you rented, and me in a black negligee and a life preserver.

426
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,404
那你记得我们说过什么吗？
Do you remember what we talked about?

427
00:39:24,571 --> 00:39:28,157
- 我们说过的一些事情　- 我会离婚的。
- We talked about a lot of things. - I mean about my getting a divorce.

428
00:39:28,324 --> 00:39:30,660
我们没有说过这个，杰夫。是你说的
We didn't talk about it, Jeff. You did.

429
00:39:30,827 --> 00:39:32,829
你不相信我，是吗？
You didn't believe me, did you?

430
00:39:32,996 --> 00:39:37,417
他们现在换了一张唱片。“音乐把她带到身边。”
They got it on a long-playing record now. "Music to String Her Along By."

431
00:39:37,584 --> 00:39:42,380
“我妻子根本不理解我。你是我碰到的让我最幸福的人”
"My wife doesn't understand me. You're the best thing that ever happened to me."

432
00:39:42,547 --> 00:39:45,842
- 这还不够嘛？弗兰。　- “相信我，宝贝，一切都会好的。”
- That's enough, Fran. - "Trust me, baby. We'll work it out."

433
00:39:46,009 --> 00:39:48,761
- 别开玩笑了　- 我没有
- You're not being funny. - I wasn't trying.

434
00:39:49,262 --> 00:39:53,224
- 弗兰，你就听我讲几分钟。　- 好吧。对不起。
- Fran, just listen to me for a minute. - All right. I'm sorry.

435
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:58,438
我今天早上去见律师了，向他问了些解决问题的方案。
I saw my lawyer this morning. I wanted his advice about the best way to handle it.

436
00:39:58,605 --> 00:40:01,107
- 解决什么问题？　- 你认为呢？
- Handle what? - What do you think?

437
00:40:02,525 --> 00:40:07,071
老实说，杰夫，我从来都没有让你离开你的妻子
Let's get something straight, Jeff. I never asked you to leave your wife.

438
00:40:07,238 --> 00:40:09,949
当然没有。你不要多想。
Of course not. You had nothing to do with it.

439
00:40:11,909 --> 00:40:14,078
你确认你是认真的吗？
Are you sure that's what you want?

440
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:18,750
当然…只要你说你还爱我
I'm sure... if you'll just tell me that you still love me.

441
00:40:21,919 --> 00:40:23,963
你知道我的心意
You know I do.

442
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:28,801
弗兰
Fran.

443
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:34,474
杰夫，亲爱的…
Jeff, darling...

444
00:40:40,897 --> 00:40:43,983
这里人太多了，我们出去吧！
It is getting crowded. Let's get out of here.

445
00:41:16,349 --> 00:41:17,850
出租车！
Taxi!

446
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:21,604
- 杰夫，我还有个约会，记得吗？　- 但是我爱你，记得吗？
- Jeff, I have that date, remember? - But I love you, remember?

447
00:41:21,771 --> 00:41:24,357
我们去哪儿？
- [Whistles] - Where are we going?

448
00:41:24,524 --> 00:41:27,360
- 不会再去那条破船吧？　- 我保证不会。
- Not back to that leaky boat? - I promise.

449
00:41:31,864 --> 00:41:34,367
西67街51号
51 West 67th.

450
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:20,246
恭喜你
Congratulations.

451
00:42:35,595 --> 00:42:38,681
你在意吗？CC·巴克斯特，是我。
Would you mind? C.C. Baxter... that's me.

452
00:42:42,101 --> 00:42:44,228
谢谢
Thank you.

453
00:42:59,452 --> 00:43:02,914
嗨，巴德男孩，恭喜你，真让人开心
Hi, Buddy-boy. Congratulations and all that jazz.

454
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,542
嘿，好家伙好了，你升职了，正如我们许诺的那样
- Hi, fellas. - Well, you made it, just like we promised.

455
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:09,879
真漂亮的办公室，看看门上的名字，地上的毯子
Quite an office. Name on the door, rug on the floor.

456
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:14,717
团队工作：是一个组织存在的前提。人人为我，我为人人
Teamwork: That's what counts in this organization. All for one and one for all.

457
00:43:14,884 --> 00:43:16,886
- 知道我什么意思吗？　- 不太清楚
- Know what I mean? - I have a vague idea.

458
00:43:17,053 --> 00:43:20,139
巴克斯特，我们对你有点失望，竟然一点感谢的表示都没有
Baxter, we're a little disappointed in you, gratitudewise.

459
00:43:20,306 --> 00:43:23,768
- 哦，我非常感谢各位的帮助　- 那你为什么把我们拒之门外呢？
- Oh, I'm very grateful. - Then why are you locking us out?

460
00:43:23,935 --> 00:43:29,482
哦，过去几个星期里对大家确有不周之处，那是因为我感冒了…
Well, it's been sort of rough the past few weeks, what with my cold and... like that.

461
00:43:29,649 --> 00:43:32,443
我们把你提上来，现在你却不理我们了
We went to bat for you. Now you won't play ball with us.

462
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:36,906
说到底，这是我的公寓，我的私人财产，不是公众的游乐场
After all, it's my apartment. It's private property, not a public playground.

463
00:43:37,073 --> 00:43:41,285
你是不是也找了一个女朋友？这没有问题，你总不会每天晚上都做爱吧！
So you got yourself a girl. That's OK with us. But not every night in the week!

464
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:43,162
你怎么能这么自私呢？
How selfish can you get?

465
00:43:43,329 --> 00:43:47,083
上个星期我不得不借我侄子的汽车，带着塞维利亚开车到泽西的汽车旅馆
Last week I had to use my nephew's car and take Sylvia to a drive-in in Jersey.

466
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:50,253
我太老了，不能那样折腾，我是说在大众汽车里
I'm too old for that sort of thing... I mean in a Volkswagen.

467
00:43:50,419 --> 00:43:53,673
我很同情你。相信我，我对此也非常的难过
I sympathize with you. Believe me, I'm very sorry.

468
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:57,093
- 你会为此更后悔的。　- 你在威胁我吗？
- You'll be a lot sorrier. - Are you threatening me?

469
00:43:57,260 --> 00:44:00,346
听着，巴克斯特，我们可以提你上来，也可以把你踢回原形
Listen, Baxter. We made you and we can break you.

470
00:44:01,597 --> 00:44:04,475
- 早上好，舍尔爵克先生。　- 早上好，先生们
- Good morning, Mr. Sheldrake. - Good morning, gentlemen.

471
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:08,729
- 巴克斯特，喜欢你的办公室吗？　- 是的，先生，非常感谢你的提携
- Baxter, do you like your office? - Yes, sir. I wanna thank you very much.

472
00:44:08,896 --> 00:44:11,774
不要谢我，都是你这里的朋友大力推荐你的
Don't thank me. Your friends here recommended you.

473
00:44:11,941 --> 00:44:15,695
我们顺便过来来祝他好运，我们知道你不会让我们失望的
- We just dropped by to wish him luck. - We know you won't let us down.

474
00:44:15,862 --> 00:44:20,658
再见，有空过来坐坐。我办公室的大门…永远对你们敞开
So long, fellas. Drop in any time. The door is always open... to my office.

475
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:23,536
我喜欢你处事的方式，巴克斯特先生
I like the way you handled that, Baxter.

476
00:44:23,703 --> 00:44:26,247
- 做经理的感觉如何？　- 哦，很好
- How does it feel to be an executive? - Oh, fine.

477
00:44:26,414 --> 00:44:30,209
- 我会努力工作来增强你对我的信心　- 我相信你会的
- I'll work hard to justify your confidence. - I'm sure you will.

478
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:35,131
关于你公寓的事情，既然你已经提升了，我们能不能多配一把钥匙
About the apartment. Now that you've got a raise, can't we afford a second key?

479
00:44:35,298 --> 00:44:37,675
- 我想没问题的　- 你知道我的秘书，奥尔森小姐？
- I guess so. - You know my secretary, Miss Olsen?

480
00:44:37,842 --> 00:44:40,636
- 哦，她也是你喜欢的人之一吗？　- 哦，不不不
- Oh, yeah. Is she the lucky girl that? - Oh, no, no.

481
00:44:40,803 --> 00:44:46,058
我只是说她是那种喜欢多管闲事的人，把钥匙递来递去的…
I just meant that she's kind of a busybody, and passing that key back and forth...

482
00:44:46,225 --> 00:44:48,811
- 万一被她发现的话…　- 你不用太谨慎了
- Why take chances? - You can't be too careful.

483
00:44:48,978 --> 00:44:51,981
对了，我想…我这里可能有一些东西是你的
Oh, I... have something I think belongs to you.

484
00:44:52,148 --> 00:44:54,650
- 我的？　- 我是说那位年轻的女士，虽然我不知道她是谁
- Me? - I mean the young lady, whoever she is.

485
00:44:54,817 --> 00:44:57,528
- 昨天晚上我回来的时候发现的　- 哦，谢谢
- I found it when I got back last night. - Oh. Thanks.

486
00:44:57,695 --> 00:45:01,240
镜子是破的。当我发现的时候就是破的
The mirror is broken. It was broken when I found it.

487
00:45:02,909 --> 00:45:05,703
- 哦，她用这镜子砸了我。　- 没事吧，先生？
- Yeah. She threw it at me. - Sir?

488
00:45:05,870 --> 00:45:08,331
你知道这是什么回事的了，他们总不会让你好过的
You know how it is. They always give you a bad time.

489
00:45:08,497 --> 00:45:09,540
哦，我知道
Yeah, I know how it is.

490
00:45:09,707 --> 00:45:14,420
你每天对着一个女孩笑，他们就认为你要和你的妻子离婚
You see a girl every week for laughs and they think you're gonna divorce your wife.

491
00:45:14,587 --> 00:45:17,757
- 我问你，这公平吗？　- 不，非常不公平
- Now I ask you, is that fair? - No, sir. It's very unfair.

492
00:45:17,924 --> 00:45:19,926
特别是对你的妻子。是的
- Especially to your wife. - Yeah.

493
00:45:20,343 --> 00:45:24,889
你知道，巴克斯特，我很羡慕你，一个单身汉，想干什么，就干什么，无所顾忌
You know, Baxter, I envy you. A bachelor, all the dames you want, no complications.

494
00:45:25,056 --> 00:45:26,599
那才是真正的生活
That's the life all right.

495
00:45:26,766 --> 00:45:29,018
- 我星期四还需要那公寓　- 明白
- Put me down for Thursday again. - Roger.

496
00:45:29,185 --> 00:45:31,437
到时候我就用那把钥匙
And I'll get that other key.

497
00:45:43,616 --> 00:45:47,453
- 圣诞快乐，到时候再联系　- 圣诞快乐，联合生活
- Merry Christmas. I'll connect you. - Merry Christmas. Consolidated Life.

498
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:49,622
圣诞快乐，我正在打电话
Merry Christmas. I'm ringing.

499
00:45:49,789 --> 00:45:51,791
喂？喂？
Yeah? Yeah?!

500
00:45:51,958 --> 00:45:53,042
哪里？
Where?

501
00:45:53,209 --> 00:45:54,418
你猜！
You bet!

502
00:45:54,585 --> 00:45:58,965
有人占住我的线路。19楼有一个晚会
Somebody watch my line. There's a swingin' party on the 19th floor!

503
00:46:01,259 --> 00:46:04,178
我们滑雪多快乐，我们坐在雪橇上
 Oh, what fun it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh

504
00:46:04,345 --> 00:46:08,099
嗨，叮叮当，叮叮当，铃儿响叮当
 Hey! Jingle bells, jingle bells, jingle all the way

505
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:11,477
我们滑雪多快乐，我们坐在雪橇上
 Oh, what fun it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh

506
00:46:27,660 --> 00:46:33,165
于是我对他说：“去你的吧，要么自己找辆大卡车要么就换个小点儿的姑娘吧”
So I said to him "Never again. Either you get yourself a bigger car or a smaller girl."

507
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:36,085
库伯利克小姐…
Miss Kubelik? Miss...

508
00:46:36,294 --> 00:46:38,462
- 圣诞快乐　- 谢谢
- Merry Christmas. - Thank you.

509
00:46:38,629 --> 00:46:41,674
- 我感觉你好像在躲着我　- 为什么会这么想呢？
- I thought you were avoiding me. - What gave you that idea?

510
00:46:41,841 --> 00:46:45,594
在6个星期里你只坐过一次我的电梯，而且还戴着帽子
In six weeks you've only been in my elevator once, and you kept on your hat.

511
00:46:45,761 --> 00:46:49,181
事实上，那天晚上我等了很久，你都没有到，这确实让我很伤心
As a matter of fact, I was rather hurt that night you stood me up.

512
00:46:49,348 --> 00:46:51,350
我知道，这的确不可原谅
I don't blame you. It was unforgivable.

513
00:46:51,517 --> 00:46:53,102
- 我原谅你了　- 你不会的
- I forgive you. - You shouldn't.

514
00:46:53,269 --> 00:46:56,689
这种事情你也没有办法的，你不可能突然对那个男人说…
You couldn't help it. You can't suddenly walk out on one man...

515
00:46:56,856 --> 00:46:59,066
因为我和另外一个男人还有一个约会
...because you have a date with another man.

516
00:46:59,233 --> 00:47:01,610
- 你做得没错　- 不要太自信
- You did the decent thing. - Don't be too sure.

517
00:47:01,777 --> 00:47:05,197
就是因为我穿的是制服，这并不能使我成为一个女童子军
Just because I wear a uniform, that doesn't make me a Girl Scout.

518
00:47:05,364 --> 00:47:10,119
第二管理助理应该是一个非常好的职位
A second administrative assistant has to be a pretty good judge of character.

519
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:12,705
而且据我所知，你非常优秀
And as far as I'm concerned, you're tops.

520
00:47:12,872 --> 00:47:17,543
我使说你非常的优雅，有气质
I mean decencywise and... otherwisewise.

521
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:19,837
干杯
Cheers.

522
00:47:21,547 --> 00:47:23,841
- 再来一杯　- 我操作电梯的时候不能喝酒
- One more. - I shouldn't drink while driving.

523
00:47:24,008 --> 00:47:29,055
你说得很对，凭借我的权利我宣布这部电梯停止工作
You're so right. By the power vested in me, I declare this elevator out of order.

524
00:47:29,221 --> 00:47:31,557
我们去和他们一起狂欢吗？
Shall we join the natives?

525
00:47:31,724 --> 00:47:35,227
- 为什么不呢，他们这么的友好　- 你还不相信吗？
- Why not? They seem friendly enough. - Don't you believe it.

526
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:39,523
这里将有人作出牺牲…白领们将东西投进计算机
There'll be human sacrifices. White-collar workers tossed into computers...

527
00:47:39,690 --> 00:47:41,901
打得全是小方孔
...and punched full of little square holes.

528
00:47:42,068 --> 00:47:44,236
- 你喝了几杯了？　- 三杯
- How many drinks did you have? - Three!

529
00:47:44,403 --> 00:47:47,573
- 我想也是的　- 等一下，我听到了流水声
- I thought so. - Wait. I hear the sound of running water.

530
00:47:47,740 --> 00:47:50,367
- 我马上就回来　- 我等你
- I'll be right back! - I'll be right here.

531
00:47:51,744 --> 00:47:53,412
嗨！
Hi!

532
00:47:53,579 --> 00:47:56,165
你好，来自堪萨斯的分部经理？
How's the branch manager from Kansas City?

533
00:47:56,332 --> 00:47:58,000
- 对不起，请再说一遍　- 我是奥尔森小姐
- I beg your pardon? - I'm Miss Olsen.

534
00:47:58,167 --> 00:48:00,086
舍尔爵克先生的秘书
Mr. Sheldrake's secretary.

535
00:48:00,252 --> 00:48:02,588
所以你不要在我面前装无辜。
So you don't have to play innocent with me.

536
00:48:02,755 --> 00:48:06,759
他曾经告诉他妻子我是来自西雅图的经理
He used to tell his wife I was the branch manager from Seattle...

537
00:48:06,926 --> 00:48:11,222
四年前当我们在一起疯狂的玩乐的时候…
...four years ago when we were having a little ring-a-ding-ding.

538
00:48:12,098 --> 00:48:16,227
- 我不知道你在说什么　- 在我之前是审计部的罗斯小姐
- I don't know what you're talking about. - Before me it was Miss Rossi in Auditing.

539
00:48:16,394 --> 00:48:19,021
在我之后是死亡险部门的科奇小姐
And after me it was Miss Koch in Disability.

540
00:48:19,188 --> 00:48:21,524
在你之前也是一个小姐，呃…
And right before you was a Miss, um...

541
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:24,026
哦，她叫什么名字，在25楼工作
Oh, what's her name? On the 25th floor.

542
00:48:24,193 --> 00:48:27,696
你应该说声对不起？为什么？你什么都没有做
- Would you excuse me? - What for? You haven't done anything.

543
00:48:27,863 --> 00:48:31,117
是他，哦，那个推销员！
It's him. Oh, what a salesman!

544
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:34,036
总是坐在那个中餐厅同样的位子…
Always the last booth in the Chinese restaurant...

545
00:48:34,203 --> 00:48:37,289
…又用同样的借口和他妻子离婚
...and the same pitch about divorcing his wife.

546
00:48:39,416 --> 00:48:43,796
然后，最后一切都鸡飞蛋打
Then, in the end, you wind up with egg foo yung on your face.

547
00:48:44,130 --> 00:48:46,090
库伯利克小姐
Miss Kubelik!

548
00:48:48,134 --> 00:48:49,885
哦，谢谢你，奥尔森小姐
Well, thank you, Miss Olsen.

549
00:48:50,052 --> 00:48:54,223
非常乐意为我们的服务姑娘稍尽绵薄之力
Always happy to do a little something for our girls in uniform.

550
00:48:55,391 --> 00:48:57,476
你还好吗？出什么事情了吗？
Are you all right? What's the matter?

551
00:48:57,643 --> 00:49:00,229
没有，只是这里人太多了
Nothing. There are just too many people here.

552
00:49:00,396 --> 00:49:04,316
为什么不到我的办公室坐坐呢？有些事情我想征求你的意见
Why don't we step into my office? There's something I want your opinion about.

553
00:49:04,483 --> 00:49:09,238
我现在已经拥有自己的办公室。我是公司第二个最年轻的经理
I have my own office now. I'm the second youngest executive in this company.

554
00:49:09,405 --> 00:49:13,159
另一个年轻人是董事长的孙子
The only one younger is a grandson of the chairman of the board.

555
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,454
觉得怎么样？
Do you mind?

556
00:49:20,624 --> 00:49:24,086
库伯利克小姐，我想听听你的真实意见
Miss Kubelik, I would like your honest opinion.

557
00:49:24,253 --> 00:49:27,506
我已经放在我办公室桌子下面一个星期了，还花了我15美元
I've had this under my desk for a week. It cost me $15.

558
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:31,010
我还没有完全准备好去戴它
I haven't been able to get up enough nerve to wear it.

559
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:41,645
这是他们说的高级经理的模样，你认为怎么样？
It's what they call the Junior Executive model. What do you think?

560
00:49:45,024 --> 00:49:47,943
我想我是不是犯了一个愚蠢的错误，呃？
I guess I made a boo-boo, huh?

561
00:49:48,110 --> 00:49:50,321
- 我觉得很好　- 真的吗？
- I like it. - Really?

562
00:49:50,488 --> 00:49:53,365
你不要觉得戴这帽子很丢人
You wouldn't be ashamed to be seen with somebody in this hat?

563
00:49:53,532 --> 00:49:57,494
- 当然不会　- 也许如果我往这边歪一点
- Of course not. - Maybe if I wore it a little to one side.

564
00:49:57,661 --> 00:50:00,372
- 那样是不是好些？　- 好多了
- Is that better? - Much better.

565
00:50:00,539 --> 00:50:03,209
既然你不怕被我看到你戴这帽子.
Since you wouldn't be ashamed to be seen with me...

566
00:50:03,375 --> 00:50:06,462
我们今天晚上出去如何，你，我，还有这高帽子
...how about goin' out tonight... you, me and the bowler?

567
00:50:06,629 --> 00:50:09,381
我们在第五大街逛逛，好好休息一下
We'll stroll down 5th Avenue, sort of break it in.

568
00:50:09,548 --> 00:50:13,385
- 今天我心情不太好　- 我明白，圣诞节不能和家人在一起
- This is a bad day for me. - I understand. Christmas and family.

569
00:50:13,552 --> 00:50:15,888
我要回去了，否则我会被炒掉的.
I'd better get back to my elevator or I'll be fired.

570
00:50:16,055 --> 00:50:19,892
不要担心，我想我在人事部还有一些影响力
Don't worry about that. I've got quite a bit of influence with Personnel.

571
00:50:20,059 --> 00:50:22,144
你认识舍尔爵克先生吗？
You know Mr. Sheldrake?

572
00:50:23,562 --> 00:50:25,898
- 怎么了？　- 他和我的关系就像这样
- Why? - He and I are like that.

573
00:50:26,065 --> 00:50:28,817
他送给我一张圣诞卡片，看到没有？
Sent me a Christmas card. See?

574
00:50:34,490 --> 00:50:37,243
很漂亮的卡片
Makes a cute picture.

575
00:50:38,202 --> 00:50:40,871
我会和舍尔爵克先生说让他提升你
I could talk to Mr. Sheldrake. Get you a promotion.

576
00:50:41,038 --> 00:50:46,752
你想做一个电梯操作班长吗？太多女孩比我优秀
- Would you like to be an elevator starter? - Too many girls have seniority over me.

577
00:50:47,127 --> 00:50:50,214
没有问题，为什么我们不讨论一下假期呢？
No problem. Why don't we discuss it over the holidays?

578
00:50:50,381 --> 00:50:54,760
我会给你打电话，邀请你出来，让大家都知道，还有我戴这顶帽子！
I could call you, pick you up, have a big unveiling. Am I wearing this right?

579
00:50:54,927 --> 00:50:57,054
我知道了，这里
I think so. Here.

580
00:50:57,221 --> 00:51:00,224
是不是翘得太厉害了？这是一家很保守的公司
It's not tilted too much? This is a conservative firm.

581
00:51:00,391 --> 00:51:03,519
我不想让人们误认为我是一个哗众取宠的人
I don't want people to think I'm an entertainer.

582
00:51:07,940 --> 00:51:10,025
怎么了？
What's the matter?

583
00:51:12,736 --> 00:51:15,281
- 你的镜子，好像破了。　- 是的，我知道
- The mirror. It's broken. - Yes, I know.

584
00:51:16,282 --> 00:51:19,285
我喜欢这样。让我可以按照我想要的方式照镜子
I like it that way. Makes me look the way I feel.

585
00:51:23,622 --> 00:51:25,749
你的电话
Your phone.

586
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:33,465
是吗？
Yes?

587
00:51:33,966 --> 00:51:35,801
哦，等一下
Uh, just a minute.

588
00:51:35,968 --> 00:51:40,556
- 如果你不介意的话，这是一个私人电话。　- 圣诞快乐
- If you don't mind, this is sort of personal. - Have a nice Christmas.

589
00:51:47,271 --> 00:51:49,315
舍尔爵克先生
Yes, Mr. Sheldrake.

590
00:51:50,399 --> 00:51:55,654
不，我没有忘，我家的圣诞树已经做好了，汤姆和杰瑞的礼物我都放在冰箱了
No, I didn't forget. The tree is up and the Tom and Jerry mix is in the refrigerator.

591
00:51:55,821 --> 00:51:57,948
是的，圣诞快乐
Yes, sir. Same to you.

592
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:27,644
嘿，你准备去哪儿，巴德小伙？
Hey! Where are you goin', Buddy-boy?

593
00:52:27,811 --> 00:52:30,022
晚会才开始
The party's just starting.

594
00:52:30,189 --> 00:52:33,525
听着，小伙子，给我安排一个时间，明天下午如何？
Listen, kid. Gimme a break. How about tomorrow afternoon?

595
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:39,281
我再也不能带她去车上做爱了，汽车没有空调？四点如何，好吗？
I can't take her to that drive-in again. The car has no heater. Four o'clock. OK?

596
00:53:15,401 --> 00:53:21,073
嗨，查理，给我一小杯波旁，快上来，我的雪橇是双人座
Hey, Charlie! Gimme a shot of bourbon, and step on it! My sleigh is double-parked!

597
00:54:28,390 --> 00:54:31,560
你给我买一杯酒，我给你放一些音乐
You buy me a drink, I'll buy you some music.

598
00:54:31,727 --> 00:54:33,812
罗姆克林斯
Rum Collins.

599
00:54:43,906 --> 00:54:45,157
呃…
Uh...

600
00:54:45,324 --> 00:54:48,994
罗姆克林斯…这些年轻母亲之一
Rum Collins and... another one of these little mothers.

601
00:55:01,131 --> 00:55:03,008
你喜欢卡斯特罗吗？
You like Castro?

602
00:55:03,175 --> 00:55:06,011
我的意思是说你对卡斯特罗的看法如何？
I mean, how do you feel about Castro?

603
00:55:06,178 --> 00:55:09,973
- 谁是卡斯特罗？　- 你知道的，古巴的大人物
- What is Castro? - You know. That big shot down in Cuba.

604
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:12,267
- 留着一个大胡子　- 他怎么了
- With the crazy beard. - What about him?

605
00:55:12,434 --> 00:55:15,687
因为据我所知，他是一个不折不扣的大流氓
Cause as far as I'm concerned, he's a no-good fink.

606
00:55:15,854 --> 00:55:19,191
两个星期之前，我给他写信他却没有给我回复
Two weeks ago I wrote him a letter. Never even answered me.

607
00:55:19,358 --> 00:55:20,317
那又怎么样？
That so?

608
00:55:20,484 --> 00:55:24,238
我让他做的就只是放米奇出来过圣诞节
All I wanted him to do was let Mickey out for Christmas.

609
00:55:24,404 --> 00:55:26,448
- 谁是米奇？　- 我丈夫
- Who's Mickey? - My husband.

610
00:55:26,615 --> 00:55:29,159
他现在在哈瓦那坐牢
He's in Havana, in jail.

611
00:55:29,326 --> 00:55:32,830
- 他参加了那次革命吗？　- 米奇不会坐那样的事情的
- Mixed up in that revolution? - Mickey would do nothin' like that.

612
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:36,708
他是一个训马师，他们让他训马
He's a jockey. They caught him dopin' a horse.

613
00:55:36,875 --> 00:55:39,211
哦，那你不要对他们抱什么希望
Well, you can't win 'em all.

614
00:55:44,341 --> 00:55:47,970
今天是圣诞前夜，整栋房子
'Twas the night before Christmas, and all through the house

615
00:55:48,136 --> 00:55:50,222
没有一点生气…
Not a creature was stirrin'...

616
00:55:50,931 --> 00:55:54,059
什么都没有，一点动静都没有
Nothin'. No action.

617
00:55:54,560 --> 00:55:56,478
极度沉闷，无聊至极
Dullsville.

618
00:55:56,645 --> 00:55:58,730
- 你结婚了吗？　- 没有
- You married? - No.

619
00:55:58,897 --> 00:56:00,983
- 有家庭吗？　- 没有
- Family? - No.

620
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:06,363
这样的一个夜晚，想你这样的幽灵走进一间空荡荡的公寓
A night like this, it sort of spooks you to walk into an empty apartment.

621
00:56:07,906 --> 00:56:12,077
我说我没有家庭，这不代表我的公寓就是空荡荡的
I said I had no family. I didn't say I had an empty apartment.

622
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:19,418
快点，弗兰，不要这样子了
Come on, Fran. Don't be that way.

623
00:56:20,085 --> 00:56:23,046
你还打算坐在这里不停地抱怨我吗？
Are you just gonna sit there and keep bawling?

624
00:56:23,213 --> 00:56:26,550
为什么不和我说话呢？你总要告诉我哪里做错了吧
You won't talk to me? You won't tell me what's wrong?

625
00:56:28,260 --> 00:56:33,265
我知道你认为我在推托你…假设当你结婚12年后
I know you think I'm stalling you but... when you've been married for 12 years...

626
00:56:33,432 --> 00:56:38,020
你能硬下心肠说“我已经厌倦了，咱们离婚吧！”
...you just don't sit down to breakfast and say "Pass the sugar. I want a divorce."

627
00:56:38,186 --> 00:56:40,772
很多事情不是想象的那么容易
It's not that easy.

628
00:56:42,024 --> 00:56:46,778
总之，现在的时机还不成熟，我儿子正在放假，岳父母也还在我家里住着
Anyway, this is the wrong time. The kids are off school, my in-laws are visiting.

629
00:56:46,945 --> 00:56:48,947
我不能现在和他们撕破脸皮，
I can't bring it up now.

630
00:56:50,782 --> 00:56:55,954
这不象你啊，弗兰，你是个非常开朗的女孩，和你在一起总是很开心的
This isn't like you, Fran. You were always such a good sport. Such fun to be with.

631
00:56:58,248 --> 00:57:02,628
对，我是一个快乐的傻瓜，总被人笑话
That's me. The happy idiot. A million laughs.

632
00:57:03,587 --> 00:57:07,883
好了，这样才对嘛，至少你能和我说话了
Well, that's a little more like it. At least you're speaking to me.

633
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:12,220
今天公司晚会我碰到了一件有趣的事情
A funny thing happened to me at the office party today.

634
00:57:12,387 --> 00:57:14,890
我碰到了你的秘书，奥尔森小姐
I ran into your secretary, Miss Olsen.

635
00:57:15,807 --> 00:57:17,934
你知道的，一个曾经和你热恋的人
You know. Ring-a-ding-ding?

636
00:57:18,977 --> 00:57:21,813
我被她气死了，我不想活了
And I laughed so much, I like to died.

637
00:57:21,980 --> 00:57:26,568
弗兰，是这件事情在困扰你吗？奥尔森小姐？都是陈年旧事了
Is that what's been bothering you, Fran? Miss Olsen? That's ancient history.

638
00:57:26,735 --> 00:57:29,821
哎呀，我的记性向来都不是太好
Well, I never was very good at history.

639
00:57:30,489 --> 00:57:34,743
让我来帮你想想，先是奥尔森小姐，然后是洛斯小姐
Let me see. There was Miss Olsen, and then there was Miss Rossi.

640
00:57:34,910 --> 00:57:37,996
不，她还在前面，奥尔森小姐，后面是科其小姐
No, she came before. Miss Koch came after Miss Olsen.

641
00:57:38,163 --> 00:57:40,499
好了，弗兰…你现在想一想
- Now, Fran... - And just think.

642
00:57:40,666 --> 00:57:44,503
这个房子里是不是还要有人像我一样成为你的幸运女孩？
Right now some lucky girl in the building is gonna come after me.

643
00:57:44,670 --> 00:57:47,422
不要说了，弗兰，我想也许是我罪有应得
OK. OK, Fran. I guess I deserved that.

644
00:57:47,589 --> 00:57:51,677
但是你问问你自己：为什么一个男人会追求这么多的女孩，这么花心？
But ask yourself: Why does a man run around with a lot of girls?

645
00:57:51,843 --> 00:57:55,597
因为他在家里不开心，因为他很孤独，这才是真正的原因
Because he's unhappy at home. Because he's lonely. That's why.

646
00:57:55,764 --> 00:57:59,017
这些都在你之前，弗兰，我现在已经不再花心了
But that was before you, Fran. I've stopped running.

647
00:58:00,519 --> 00:58:04,648
我怎么会这么愚蠢呢？你肯定在想我早就被你吃透了
How could I be so stupid? You'd think I would've learned by now.

648
00:58:04,815 --> 00:58:09,361
当你爱上一个已婚男人的时候，就注定没有好结局。
When you're in love with a married man, you shouldn't wear mascara.

649
00:58:10,112 --> 00:58:13,240
弗兰，今天是圣诞夜，我们不要吵架，好吗？
It's Christmas Eve, Fran. Let's not fight, huh?

650
00:58:15,534 --> 00:58:18,036
- 圣诞快乐！　- 这是什么？
- Merry Christmas. - What is it?

651
00:58:23,500 --> 00:58:26,211
我们中餐厅朋友送的
Oh. Our friend at the Chinese restaurant.

652
00:58:27,379 --> 00:58:32,718
- 谢谢，弗兰，我们最好把它放在这里。　- 是的。
- Thanks, Fran. We'd better keep it here. - Yeah, we'd better.

653
00:58:33,468 --> 00:58:35,554
对了，我也为你准备了一份礼物
Oh, I have a present for you.

654
00:58:35,721 --> 00:58:40,058
我不知道给你买什么东西好，另外…我也很不喜欢去逛街买东西，因此…
I didn't know what to get you. Besides, it's kind of awkward for me shopping, so...

655
00:58:40,225 --> 00:58:43,729
我给你100美元，你自己看着喜欢什么就买什么吧！
Here's $100. You go and buy yourself something.

656
00:58:48,692 --> 00:58:51,903
在伯格道夫专卖店有一些很好的鳄鱼皮包
They have some nice alligator bags at Bergdorf's.

657
00:59:03,665 --> 00:59:07,753
想不到现在这么晚了，都已经七点差十分了，我现在必须去赶火车去了
I didn't realize it was so late. It's quarter to seven. I mustn't miss my train.

658
00:59:07,919 --> 00:59:12,507
如果不是我们已经浪费了这么多时间的话，我可能现在已经到家修剪圣诞树了
If we hadn't wasted all this time... I have to get home and trim the tree.

659
00:59:13,049 --> 00:59:16,887
那好，我就当作是我陪你的报酬
OK. I just thought, as long as it was paid for...

660
00:59:17,054 --> 00:59:19,097
弗兰，不要这样说话
Don't ever talk like that, Fran.

661
00:59:19,264 --> 00:59:23,393
不要把自己说得这么不值钱，100美元？我才不会这么便宜的！
- Don't make yourself out to be cheap. - $100? I don't call that cheap.

662
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:27,606
你是不是还给这间公寓的人付过钱了？
And you must be paying somebody something for the use of the apartment.

663
00:59:27,773 --> 00:59:29,900
住嘴，弗兰
Stop it, Fran.

664
00:59:30,942 --> 00:59:33,028
杰夫，你快赶不上火车了
You'll miss your train, Jeff.

665
00:59:41,620 --> 00:59:43,205
你和我一起出去吗？
Are you coming?

666
00:59:43,371 --> 00:59:45,957
不，你先走，我还要补补妆
No, you run along. I'm gonna fix my face.

667
00:59:46,124 --> 00:59:48,627
不要忘记关灯，我们星期一见
Don't forget to kill the lights. See you Monday.

668
00:59:48,794 --> 00:59:52,380
好的，星期一…星期四
Sure. Monday... and Thursday...

669
00:59:52,547 --> 00:59:55,801
然后又是星期一，又是星期四
...and Monday again, and Thursday again.

670
00:59:57,761 --> 01:00:00,639
弗兰，这种情况不会很久的
It won't always be like this, Fran.

671
01:00:00,806 --> 01:00:02,933
我爱你
I love you.

672
01:00:03,099 --> 01:00:05,393
小心一点，不要沾到口红了
Careful. Lipstick.

673
01:00:06,645 --> 01:00:08,772
圣诞快乐
Merry Christmas.

674
01:02:36,127 --> 01:02:39,673
- 快喝完，要关门了　- 还早呢，查理
- Drink up, pop. It's closing time. - But it's early, Charlie.

675
01:02:39,839 --> 01:02:43,385
- 难道你不知道今天是什么日子吗？　- 我知道，查理
- Don't you know what night this is? - I know, Charlie. I know.

676
01:02:43,551 --> 01:02:45,637
我为一个团体工作
I work for the outfit.

677
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:53,979
嗨，快停下来，听到没有？快回家
Hey, knock it off, will ya? Go home.

678
01:03:02,153 --> 01:03:04,406
出去！出去！
O-U-T. Out!

679
01:03:09,327 --> 01:03:11,997
我们去哪里？我的地方还是你的？
Where'll we go? My place or yours?

680
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:18,003
最好到我那里去，他们每个人都这样干
Might as well go to mine. Everybody else does.

681
01:03:29,681 --> 01:03:35,020
可怜的宝贝，我还在想那个在哈瓦那坐牢的可怜虫
